        <main class="content">
            <div class="doc-header" id="introduction">
                <h1 class="doc-title">Documentation</h1>
                <p class="doc-description">
                    Complete guide to setting up and using Sentinel bot for your Discord server. 
                    Learn about features, configuration, and best practices for server security.
                </p>
            </div>

            <section class="doc-section" id="setup">
                <h2>Setup Guide</h2>
                <p>
                    Getting started with Sentinel is quick and easy. Follow these steps to add the bot 
                    to your server and configure your first security settings.
                </p>

                <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Administrator permissions in your Discord server</li>
                    <li>Understanding of basic Discord permissions and roles</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Installation Steps</h3>
                <ol class="steps">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Invite the Bot</strong><br>
                        Click the "Add to Server" button and select your server from the dropdown. 
                        Make sure to grant all requested permissions for full functionality.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Login to Dashboard</strong><br>
                        Visit the web dashboard and login with Discord. Select your server from the list 
                        to access the configuration panel.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Configure Settings</strong><br>
                        Set up your logging channels, moderation settings, and security features through 
                        the dashboard or using <span class="inline-code">/settings</span> command.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Test Features</strong><br>
                        Try basic commands like <span class="inline-code">/help</span> and 
                        <span class="inline-code">/botinfo</span> to verify the bot is working correctly.
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <div class="info-box-title">
                        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                        Pro Tip
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        For best results, place the Sentinel bot role near the top of your role hierarchy. 
                        This ensures it can moderate users with lower roles.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="quickstart">
                <h2>Quick Start</h2>
                <p>Get up and running in minutes with these essential configurations:</p>

                <h4>1. Set Up Logging</h4>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/serversettings<br>→ Select "Logging Channel"<br>→ Choose your logs channel</code>
                </div>

                <h4>2. Enable Auto-Moderation</h4>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/serversettings<br>→ Toggle "Auto-Moderation"<br>→ Configure blocked words</code>
                </div>

                <h4>3. Configure Anti-Spam</h4>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/serversettings<br>→ Toggle "Anti-Spam System"<br>→ Set thresholds</code>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="auto-moderation">
                <h2>Auto-Moderation</h2>
                <p>
                    Sentinel's auto-moderation system automatically detects and removes inappropriate content, 
                    spam, and rule violations without manual intervention.
                </p>

                <h3>Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Blocked Words:</strong> Custom word blacklist with wildcard support (e.g., *bad*)</li>
                    <li><strong>Zalgo Detection:</strong> Prevents zalgo text and Unicode abuse</li>
                    <li><strong>Emoji Spam:</strong> Limits excessive emoji usage in messages</li>
                    <li><strong>Mass Mentions:</strong> Blocks messages with too many user/role mentions</li>
                    <li><strong>Link Filtering:</strong> Optional restriction of external links</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Configuration</h3>
                <p>Access auto-moderation settings through the dashboard or use these commands:</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/blockedwords add [word]     # Add blocked word<br>/blockedwords remove [word]  # Remove blocked word<br>/blockedwords list           # View all blocked words</code>
                </div>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <div class="warning-box-title">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                        Important
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Users with <strong>Manage Messages</strong> permission are exempt from auto-moderation. 
                        Use <span class="inline-code">/whitelist</span> to exempt specific users.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="anti-nuke">
                <h2>Anti-Nuke Protection</h2>
                <p>
                    Protect your server from malicious attacks with real-time detection of mass deletions, 
                    excessive bans, and other destructive actions.
                </p>

                <h3>Protected Actions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Channel Deletion:</strong> Detects mass channel deletion attempts</li>
                    <li><strong>Role Deletion:</strong> Monitors excessive role removals</li>
                    <li><strong>Ban Waves:</strong> Catches mass ban attempts</li>
                    <li><strong>Kick Spam:</strong> Prevents rapid member kicks</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Response Actions</h3>
                <p>When a nuke attempt is detected, Sentinel can:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Immediately remove dangerous permissions from the attacker</li>
                    <li>Ban the offending user automatically</li>
                    <li>Send alerts to your configured log channel</li>
                    <li>Notify server administrators via DM</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <div class="info-box-title">
                        <i class="fas fa-shield-halved"></i>
                        Best Practice
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Enable anti-nuke protection immediately after adding the bot. Set thresholds 
                        appropriate for your server size (smaller servers should use lower thresholds).
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="anti-spam">
                <h2>Anti-Spam System</h2>
                <p>
                    Advanced spam detection monitors message patterns and automatically times out 
                    users who spam or flood channels.
                </p>

                <h3>Detection Methods</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Duplicate Messages:</strong> Tracks identical message repetition</li>
                    <li><strong>Message Rate:</strong> Monitors messages per second</li>
                    <li><strong>Image Spam:</strong> Detects rapid image/attachment posting</li>
                    <li><strong>Link Spam:</strong> Prevents excessive link sharing</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Configurable Thresholds</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code># Configure via dashboard:<br>Max Messages: 5 messages in 5 seconds<br>Max Duplicates: 3 identical messages<br>Max Images: 3 images in 10 seconds</code>
                </div>

                <h3>Whitelist System</h3>
                <p>
                    Exempt trusted users, roles, or channels from anti-spam using the whitelist command:
                </p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/whitelist add @user     # Exempt a user<br>/whitelist remove @user  # Remove exemption</code>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="global-bans">
                <h2>Global Ban Network</h2>
                <p>
                    Join a cross-server ban network to protect your community from known troublemakers 
                    across multiple Discord servers.
                </p>

                <h3>How It Works</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Enable global bans in your server settings</li>
                    <li>When you globally ban a user, they're added to the network</li>
                    <li>Other servers with global bans enabled will automatically ban them</li>
                    <li>Users can appeal through the built-in appeal system</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Issuing Global Bans</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/globalban @user [reason]  # Issue cross-server ban<br>/globalbans                 # View all global bans</code>
                </div>

                <h3>Appeal System</h3>
                <p>Users can submit appeals which server administrators can review:</p>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <code>/appeal [reason]            # User submits appeal<br>/reviewappeal @user approve  # Accept appeal<br>/reviewappeal @user deny     # Reject appeal</code>
                </div>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <div class="warning-box-title">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                        Caution
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Global bans are powerful. Only use them for severe violations like raiding, 
                        harassment, or illegal content. Misuse may result in removal from the network.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="logging">
                <h2>Logging System</h2>
                <p>
                    Comprehensive audit logs track all server activity, moderation actions, and security events.
                </p>

                <h3>Logged Events</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Messages:</strong> Edits, deletions, bulk deletes</li>
                    <li><strong>Members:</strong> Joins, leaves, nickname changes</li>
                    <li><strong>Roles:</strong> Role additions, removals, updates</li>
                    <li><strong>Channels:</strong> Creation, deletion, permission changes</li>
                    <li><strong>Moderation:</strong> Bans, kicks, timeouts, warnings</li>
                    <li><strong>Security:</strong> Anti-nuke triggers, spam detections</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Setup</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Create a dedicated logging channel (e.g., #mod-logs)</li>
                    <li>Configure it in dashboard or via <span class="inline-code">/serversettings</span></li>
                    <li>Ensure only moderators can view this channel</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <div class="info-box-title">
                        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                        Tip
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Create separate channels for different log types (moderation logs, member logs, 
                        message logs) for better organization in large servers.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="dashboard">
                <h2>Web Dashboard</h2>
                <p>
                    Manage your entire server configuration through a beautiful, intuitive web interface 
                    without typing commands.
                </p>

                <h3>Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Visual Configuration:</strong> Select roles and channels from dropdowns</li>
                    <li><strong>Real-Time Updates:</strong> Changes apply instantly without bot restart</li>
                    <li><strong>Bulk Editing:</strong> Add/remove multiple blocked words at once</li>
                    <li><strong>Quick Actions:</strong> Save with Ctrl+S, toggle features with one click</li>
                    <li><strong>Mobile Friendly:</strong> Full functionality on phones and tablets</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Accessing the Dashboard</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Visit the dashboard URL (linked in bot status)</li>
                    <li>Click "Login with Discord"</li>
                    <li>Authorize the OAuth2 connection</li>
                    <li>Select your server from the server list</li>
                    <li>Configure settings visually</li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="server-settings">
                <h2>Server Settings</h2>
                <p>
                    Configure all aspects of Sentinel's behavior for your server through settings.
                </p>

                <h3>Essential Settings</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Logging Channel:</strong> Where logs are sent</li>
                    <li><strong>Moderator Role:</strong> Role with moderation permissions</li>
                    <li><strong>Auto-Moderation:</strong> Enable/disable content filtering</li>
                    <li><strong>Anti-Spam:</strong> Toggle spam protection</li>
                    <li><strong>Anti-Nuke:</strong> Enable attack prevention</li>
                    <li><strong>Global Bans:</strong> Join cross-server ban network</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Advanced Options</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Custom blocked word patterns</li>
                    <li>Spam detection thresholds</li>
                    <li>Whitelisted users/roles/channels</li>
                    <li>Punishment escalation settings</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="permissions">
                <h2>Permissions</h2>
                <p>
                    Sentinel requires specific permissions to function properly. Here's what each permission is used for:
                </p>

                <h3>Required Permissions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Manage Server:</strong> Access server settings and configuration</li>
                    <li><strong>Manage Roles:</strong> Remove dangerous roles during nuke attempts</li>
                    <li><strong>Manage Channels:</strong> Lock/unlock channels, create logs</li>
                    <li><strong>Kick Members:</strong> Execute kick commands</li>
                    <li><strong>Ban Members:</strong> Execute ban commands and global bans</li>
                    <li><strong>Moderate Members:</strong> Issue timeouts and manage moderation</li>
                    <li><strong>Manage Messages:</strong> Delete rule-breaking messages, bulk purge</li>
                    <li><strong>Read Messages:</strong> Monitor for auto-moderation triggers</li>
                    <li><strong>Send Messages:</strong> Send moderation notifications</li>
                    <li><strong>Embed Links:</strong> Display rich embed responses</li>
                    <li><strong>View Audit Log:</strong> Track who made changes for logging</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <div class="warning-box-title">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                        Permission Hierarchy
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        The bot's role must be higher than the roles of users you want to moderate. 
                        Users with roles higher than the bot cannot be timed out, kicked, or banned.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="troubleshooting">
                <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
                <p>Common issues and their solutions:</p>

                <h3>Bot Not Responding</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Verify the bot is online (green status in member list)</li>
                    <li>Check if the bot has required permissions in that channel</li>
                    <li>Try re-inviting the bot with the correct permission scope</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Cannot Moderate Certain Users</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensure bot's role is higher than the target user's highest role</li>
                    <li>Check if the user has Administrator permission (cannot be moderated)</li>
                    <li>Verify the bot has required moderation permissions</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Auto-Moderation Not Working</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Confirm auto-moderation is enabled in settings</li>
                    <li>Check if the user is whitelisted or has mod permissions</li>
                    <li>Verify blocked words are configured correctly</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Dashboard Login Issues</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Clear browser cache and cookies</li>
                    <li>Ensure you have Manage Server permission</li>
                    <li>Try a different browser or incognito mode</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="doc-section" id="faq">
