                <h4>Q: Is Sentinel free to use?</h4>
                <p>Yes, Sentinel is completely free with all features included.</p>

                <h4>Q: Can I customize the bot's responses?</h4>
                <p>Currently, custom messages are not supported, but this feature is planned for a future update.</p>

                <h4>Q: How many servers can use Sentinel?</h4>
                <p>There's no limit. Sentinel can be added to unlimited servers.</p>

                <h4>Q: Does Sentinel store message content?</h4>
                <p>No, Sentinel only stores metadata (timestamps, user IDs) for moderation logs. Message content is not stored.</p>

                <h4>Q: Can I self-host Sentinel?</h4>
                <p>The source code is not currently public, but this may change in the future.</p>

                <h4>Q: What happens if the bot goes offline?</h4>
                <p>Your server settings are preserved. When the bot comes back online, all configurations will still be active.</p>

                <h4>Q: Can I suggest new features?</h4>
                <p>Absolutely! Join our support server (linked in bot status) to submit feature requests.</p>
